key "FrankPond"
literal "false"

\end_inset

), it is worth noting that relative income has been of interest to economists
 since at least as far back as 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Duesenberry1949"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "VeblenLeisureClass"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 While the relevance of relative concerns has been seldom disputed, there
 is a disconnect between the descriptive theories that consider the effects
 of the immediate context of the consumer and the theories of economic growth
 (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "KayRadicalUncertainty2020,SanjitDhamiBehavioural2016"
