The literature on positional consumption has - however - maintained that
 much of status competition leads to social waste (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ireland_signals,FrankPond,HirschSocialLimits"
literal "false"

\end_inset

).
 As 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "HirschSocialLimits"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 points out, “when everyone stands on tiptoe, no one sees better”.
 The view of status consumption as social waste has been relevant for studies
 on conspicuous consumption (see 
